Genomic Domain

Source: vignettes/genomic-domain.Rmd
genomic-domain.Rmd

Genomics Domain Vocabularies

The following vocabularies related to genomics concepts are identified.

library(chariot)
genomic_vocabularies <- 
queryAthena("SELECT vocabulary_id,COUNT(*) FROM omop_vocabulary.concept WHERE LOWER(concept_class_id) LIKE '%variant%' GROUP BY vocabulary_id;")
#> [2021-08-19 23:07:55]    Connected to 'athena'
#> [2021-08-19 23:07:55]    Loading Cache...
#> [2021-08-19 23:07:55]    Cached SQL: SELECT vocabulary_id,COUNT(*) FROM omop_vocabulary.concept WHERE LOWER(concept_class_id) LIKE '%variant%' GROUP BY vocabulary_id;
#> [2021-08-19 23:07:55]    Cached resultset found...
#> [2021-08-19 23:07:55]    Postgres connection to 'athena' closed
genomic_vocabularies
#> # A tibble: 7 x 2
#>   vocabulary_id  count
#>   <chr>          <dbl>
#> 1 CGI              323
#> 2 CIViC            988
#> 3 ClinVar         8072
#> 4 JAX             7855
#> 5 NCIt             527
#> 6 OMOP Extension 76001
#> 7 OncoKB          5569

An omop.relationships S4 class object is fetched for these vocabularies.

library(chariotViz)
omop_relationships <- 
  fetch_omop_relationships(
    !!!genomic_vocabularies$vocabulary_id,
    version_key = get_version_key())
#> ℹ Getting total concept class counts
#> ✓ Getting total concept class counts [532ms]
#> 
#> ℹ Getting total vocabulary counts
#> ✓ Getting total vocabulary counts [524ms]
#> 
omop_nodes_and_edges <- 
  create_nodes_and_edges(omop_relationships = omop_relationships)

omop_nodes_and_edges <- 
  omop_nodes_and_edges %>% 
  add_tooltip() %>%
  map_node_attributes() %>% 
  map_edge_attributes()
#> ℹ Shape from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ℹ Style from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ℹ Color from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ℹ Fillcolor from: vocabulary_id
#> ! 4 values not mapped: CGI, CIM10, Read, and UK Biobank. Mapping to `other` value 'gray20'.
#> ℹ Fontcolor from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ℹ 3 constant attributes added: fontsize, width, and height.
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ✓ All 3 unique values mapped.
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ℹ 2 constant attributes added: fontsize and len.

omop_graph <- 
  construct_graph(omop_nodes_and_edges)

chariotViz(
  omop_graph = omop_graph,
  force = TRUE, 
  width = 1500,
  height = 2000
)
#>                              ─────────────────────
#>                                n nodes   n edges  
#>                              ─────────────────────
#>                                     45        77  
#>                              ─────────────────────

After remapping fillcolor by domain, it is evident that some of these vocabularies cross multiple domains, specifically Condition and Observation.

omop_graph <- 
  remap_fillcolor_by_domain(omop_graph = omop_graph)
#> ✓ All 4 unique values mapped.
chariotViz(
  omop_graph = omop_graph,
  force = TRUE,

  height = 2000

A filter is applied for Measurement domains only.

omop_relationships <- 
omop_relationships %>% 
  filter_omop_relationships(
    domain_id_1 == "Measurement",
    domain_id_2 == "Measurement"
  )
omop_nodes_and_edges <- 
  create_nodes_and_edges(omop_relationships = omop_relationships)

The relationships are subset based on whether they are lateral, taxonomical, or mapping.

Mapping Relationships

omop_relationships_mapping <- 
omop_relationships %>% 
  filter_for_mapping_relationships() %>% 
  # Filtered out because it is a bad data capture using the regex for all variant concept classes
  filter_omop_relationships(concept_class_id_1 != "Lab Test")

omop_nodes_and_edges_mapping <- 
  create_nodes_and_edges(omop_relationships_mapping)

omop_nodes_and_edges_mapping <- 
  omop_nodes_and_edges_mapping %>% 
  add_tooltip() %>%
  map_node_attributes() %>% 
  map_edge_attributes()

The Maps to relationship is isolated to see how Variants represented in normal vocabularies are normalized to the OMOP Extension.

omop_relationships_mapping <- 
omop_relationships_mapping %>% 
  filter_for_mapping_relationships() %>% 
  # Filtered out because it is a bad data capture using the regex for all variant concept classes
  filter_omop_relationships(relationship_id == "Maps to")

  mutate_edges(label = " ")

Example concepts are added for each node.

omop_graph <- 
  omop_graph %>% 
  append_concept_examples(sample_size = 3)

  omop_graph = omop_graph,
  force = TRUE
)

Lateral Relationships

omop_relationships_lateral <- 
omop_relationships %>% 
  filter_for_lateral_relationships() %>% 
  # Filtered out because it is a bad data capture using the regex for all variant concept classes
  filter_omop_relationships(concept_class_id_1 != "Precoordinated pair",
                            vocabulary_id_1 != "NCIt")

omop_nodes_and_edges_lateral <- 
  create_nodes_and_edges(omop_relationships_lateral)

omop_nodes_and_edges_lateral <- 
  omop_nodes_and_edges_lateral %>% 
  add_tooltip() %>%
  map_node_attributes() %>% 
  map_edge_attributes() 
#> ℹ Shape from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 1 unique value mapped.
#> ℹ Style from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 1 unique value mapped.

#> ✓ All 1 unique value mapped.
#> ℹ Fillcolor from: vocabulary_id
#> ✓ All 1 unique value mapped.
#> ℹ Fontcolor from: standard_concept
#> ✓ All 1 unique value mapped.
#> ℹ 3 constant attributes added: fontsize, width, and height.
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ✓ All 1 unique value mapped.
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ✓ All 2 unique values mapped.
#> ℹ 2 constant attributes added: fontsize and len.

omop_graph <- 
  construct_graph(omop_nodes_and_edges_lateral,
                  attr_theme = "lr") %>% 
  remap_fillcolor_by_concept_class(fillcolor_map = c(`Transcript Variant` = "cadetblue",
                                                     `Protein Variant` = "indianred",
                                                     `Genomic Variant` = "mediumpurple"))
#> ✓ All 3 unique values mapped.
